<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4700] @Field variable can&apos;t be referred from closure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4700</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;attached code &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.Field

@Field def xxx = 3

foo = {
  println xxx
}

foo()

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;generate following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caught: BUG! exception in phase &apos;class generation&apos; in source unit &apos;/Users/uehaj/tmp/bug.groovy&apos; tried to get a variable with the name xxx as stack variable, but a variable with this name was not created&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

</description>
                <environment>Mac OS X</environment>
